-- IKB to Eliminate One in Six Employees, Rheinische Post Reports
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2012-02-06T23:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/ikb-to-eliminate-one-in-six-employees-rheinische-post-reports.html
IKB Deutsche Industriebank AG  will
reduce the number of its employees by 200 to around 1,000  to
reduce costs,  Rheinische Post  reported in a preview of an
article to be published today, citing unidentified people within
the company.  IKB spokesman Joerg chittka declined to comment on the
report when telephoned by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Webb in Frankfurt 
 awebb25@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chad Thomas at 
 cthomas16@bloomberg.net . 